text: Toholampi is a municipality in Central Ostrobothnia, Finland. As of 31 December 2023, 2,849 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Kannus, Kokkola, Lestijärvi and Sievi. Toholampi was founded in 1865. == Other websites == * Municipality of Toholampi – Official website Category:Municipalities of Central Ostrobothnia Category:1865 establishments in Finland
